                            "aonid": 60
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "manipulate",
                            "alt": "manipulate",
                            "game-obj": "Traits",
                            "aonid": 104
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "mental",
                            "alt": "mental",
                            "game-obj": "Traits",
                            "aonid": 106
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "Word On The Street",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Privy to all sorts of conversations from passersby, the downtrodden can provide eyes and ears on the street. Finding a reliable contact can give a character a circumstance bonus to checks to Gather Information if they return to that source. This bonus is usually +1, but could be +2 or +3 if the contact lingers in a market where influential politicians shop, sweeps a noble estate, or the like.  \n  \n Befriending NPCs in advance can also help the heroes in action scenes. A friendly urchin might show a character a shortcut to catch an escaping enemy, a crowd of fans who frequent a bard's performances might throw rocks to distract someone trying to fight the bard, and so on.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 214",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 214",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 214
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Advice and Rules",
                        "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                    },
                    "links": [
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Gather Information",
                            "alt": "Gather Information",
                            "game-obj": "Actions",
                            "aonid": 49
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "text": "Unfortunately, every society has people living on its fringes. While good communities work to grant aid and respite to their downtrodden, sometimes\u2014due to economic downturn, famine, or war\u2014the ranks of the less fortunate exceed the community's capacity to support them. In heartless neutral and evil societies, poverty is seen as an inevitability that can never be truly eradicated, or even worse, as a tool to be manipulated for political gain.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 214",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 214",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 214
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
